The first wave of highest sanctions by the FFP hit in 2014 PSG along with Manchester City, owned by the Abu Dhabi group.
The PSG received a €60 million ($82 million) fine - which was later reduced to €20 million - and an order to reduce the Champions League team to 21 players in the 2014-2015 season, instead of 25 players.
UEFA is wary of teams that may attempt to circumvent financial regulators by increasing their income through companies associated with club owners.
Thus, even if the Qatari company sponsors the PSG once the funding exceeds the standard market rate, UEFA has the right to prohibit the settlement of the amount.
