The state is counting on citizens to defend the state.
They'll support their training.
With financial support for associations used in the defense of the state, with voluntary shooting training or with a team of training trainers, the substantive intention of the Citizens' Preparedness Act is envisaged to defend the state.
The Ministry of Defence, which was tasked with processing it from the government, promises that it will be able to increase the physical prowess of Czechs and their abilities, which the state could then use in crisis situations.
