For example, the state would financially or materially support the associations of amateurs, gunmen or cynologists and would enable them to increase their members' capabilities.
In return, he would obtain data on people who, if necessary, are willing to lose the country at a time of crisis to help, and on their abilities or material equipment.
There could also be accredited instructors to help associations and other interested parties in training or education.
It is also expected to organize discussions with war veterans or people who have behaved heroically.
One possible option assumes that a new office would be established to be in charge of the administration and coordination of the project.
The authors of the proposal stress that the participation of people should be voluntary and the state would use their capabilities only after the state of threat has been declared.
"The whole concept must respect the gradual blurring of previously obvious borders between different types of threats," the intention is to refer to the dangers of so-called hybrid threats.
Ministerial officials have noted that it is therefore necessary to focus on supporting as wide a range of capabilities as possible, not just those of the military.
"The primary objective of the project is to create a very broad base that allows every citizen to respond skillfully to situations threatening the sovereignty of the state or the lives, health and property of persons, to protect himself or to contribute to the protection of others, and not to make it difficult for the armed forces of the Czech Republic to carry out their tasks," he states.
